I’m looking forward to watching the Lakers v Mavs to see Luka Doncic against LeBron James. It will be amazing to see them both facing each other again with Luka now being a more experienced player in the league. This game will be a big show for NBA fans around the world.
Nafy Amar Fall, Wiwsport (Senegal): Right off the bat they are the favorites this season. Certainly, there have been departures, but given the recruiting process, the Lakers are clearly showing that they want to keep their trophy. Getting LeBron James, Anthony Davis, Montrezl Harrel, Dennis Schröder, Marc Gasol and Wesley Matthews together on a team is tough. And they will not hesitate to show their supremacy. They just need to forget about that title they won three months ago and focus on the new season.
Brooklyn Nets v Boston Celtics. We can't wait for Kevin Durant's first outing. It will be a return of the great KD to the floor 18 months after his tendon rupture. Next to him is superstar Kyrie Irving who promises to respond on the court as well. And Kyrie will face his old team. They will face the Celtics of Tacko Fall, very followed by the Senegalese via wiwsport.com. And Boston is coming off of a good season.
Nicasius Agwanda, Clouds Media (Tanzania): LeBron James must be highly motivated heading into the new season. First of all, his team is stacked and in my personal opinion this might be the best squad he’s had his whole career. Maybe he had the best two supporting casts at the Heat, but this team is well spread out and the bench is solid. With his mentality, LeBron has a chance to win it all, but other than how other people feel, I have a different opinion on the Clippers. They had a best roster curse last season and every player thought it was big enough to hold a key part in every game. Now they’ll be competitive and can pose a great threat. Another threat for LeBron should be the Denver Nuggets, who are young and deep. One thing that I know for sure is, LeBron is looking at what KD does this season. That’s a match up we need in The Finals.



