Woury Diallo, Le Quotidien (Senegal): I think the Lakers will need to have the same start to the season as they had last year. With a 72-game shortened season, it is important not to lose the ground against other competitors. As the reigning champions, they will be the team to beat, but will have to fight to win the back-to-back title. Unfortunately, with the departures of Dwight Howard and Javale McGee, despite the arrival of Marc Gasol, the Lakers are at risk of suffering on the defensive end of the floor. It is where Marc Gasol will have a very important role to play. It is up to him to quickly find his feet within the team and make his presence felt.
Elias Makori, Nation.Africa  (Kenya): Keep a healthy roster, especially the bench players. LeBron’s duo with Anto Davis is almost unstoppable. The Lakers bench is stronger and deeper than any other in the league; so much so that there’s a game Carusso almost never played and Cuz has had a great pre-season…Lakers vs Mavs: It would be interesting to see how “heir apparent” Luka will cope against LeBron with all the pre-season talk. Luka is getting into his third NBA season and has most certainly matured and all eyes will be on how he guns for a possibly MVP award this seasoN.



